      "statePath": "/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/data/agent-sessions/session_5eb07fcd-6ce4-4b07-b2d6-99e655726b21/runs/run_1a0e5eb9-1753-4095-a87d-1852e1cbb6be/state.json",
      "messagePath": "/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/data/agent-sessions/session_5eb07fcd-6ce4-4b07-b2d6-99e655726b21/runs/run_1a0e5eb9-1753-4095-a87d-1852e1cbb6be/last-message.txt",
      "configPath": "/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/data/agent-sessions/session_5eb07fcd-6ce4-4b07-b2d6-99e655726b21/runs/run_1a0e5eb9-1753-4095-a87d-1852e1cbb6be/config.json"
    },
    {
      "id": "run_6fcb4c78-eb2c-4902-b373-c4dfe9dcef42",
      "sessionId": "session_5eb07fcd-6ce4-4b07-b2d6-99e655726b21",
      "mode": "start",
      "prompt": "Root cause is in [agent-session-runner.mjs](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/scripts/agent-session-runner.mjs#L50). Initial runs call `codex exec ... --sandbox <mode>`, but follow-up runs call `codex exec resume ...` without reapplying the stored sandbox. The session still persists the chosen sandbox in [agent-sessions.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.ts#L477) and [agent-sessions.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.ts#L527), so the UI keeps showing `workspace-write` even though resumed runs fall back to the CLI default, which is effectively read-only.\r\n\r\nThe fix is to map the stored sandbox onto the resume-specific flags that `codex exec resume --help` exposes:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nfunction buildCodexArgs(config) {\r\n\tconst args = [];\r\n\r\n\tif (config.mode === 'message') {\r\n\t\targs.push('exec', 'resume', '--json', '--skip-git-repo-check');\r\n\r\n\t\tif (config.sandbox === 'workspace-write') {\r\n\t\t\targs.push('--full-auto');\r\n\t\t} else if (config.sandbox === 'danger-full-access') {\r\n\t\t\targs.push('--dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox');\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\tif (config.model) {\r\n\t\t\targs.push('-m', config.model);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\targs.push(config.threadId, '-o', config.messagePath, config.prompt);\r\n\t\treturn args;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\t// existing start-session path stays as-is\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI tried to apply that directly, but this turn’s host sandbox is read-only, so writes were rejected. That reproduces the exact class of problem you described. If you reopen me in a write-enabled session, I can land this patch and add a regression test in [agent-sessions.spec.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.spec.ts#L1) so resume args are covered for `read-only`, `workspace-write`, and `danger-full-access`.",
      "requestedThreadId": null,
